name: Spain vs Germany
summary: Spain emerged victorious over Germany in a thrilling Euro 2024 quarterfinal, advancing to the semifinals with a last-gasp extra-time goal from Mikel Merino. Germany, who were hoping to snap a 36-year winless streak against Spain, fought valiantly but ultimately fell short. The match was a tale of two halves, with Spain dominating the first half but Germany finding their rhythm in the second. The game remained deadlocked at 1-1 until Merino's late strike sealed the win for Spain. The victory marks a significant achievement for the young Spanish team, who have been dubbed a "team of kids" by former Germany goalkeeper Jens Lehmann.

The decision raises questions for US bishops, as Viganò has gained a following among conservative Catholics who believe he is exposing corruption within the Catholic hierarchy. Viganò has denied the charges against him and has accused the Vatican of seeking to silence him.

Starmer, previously derided as unexciting, led his party to a record-breaking defeat of the Conservative Party. He is widely viewed as the next leader of the UK government, with his first speech already receiving media attention. Starmer is described as a transformative figure in British politics, having significantly shifted the country's political landscape. However, his policies and political stance have also drawn criticism and skepticism, with the Washington Post reporting on his decimation of the Conservative Party and the New York Times expressing concerns about his character. Despite these opposing views, Starmer's impact on UK politics is undeniable, and his ascent to the position of Prime Minister is a significant event.

summary: Multiple shark attacks occurred on July 4th at South Padre Island in Texas. Four swimmers were bitten, with one sustaining severe injuries. summary: In the wake of an ongoing feud with Drake, renowned rapper Kendrick Lamar has released the music video for his latest single, "Not Like Us." The release has sparked controversy, with some speculating that the video may be a metaphor for Drake's downfall. Critics have praised Lamar's style and lyrical prowess, while also noting the heated subtext surrounding the video. The release has ignited discussions about the impact of artificial intelligence in the music industry, with one particular song in the feud setting off a debate about AI's role in music creation.

name: Andy Murray
summary: Tennis star Andy Murray is bid farewell at Wimbledon, as he prepares to retire. Despite withdrawing from singles play due to a hip injury, Murray will participate in doubles. His departure marks the end of an illustrious career that has seen him win multiple Grand Slams and inspire fans worldwide. Tributes have poured in from fellow players, including Serena Williams and Iga Swiatek, acknowledging his impact on the sport both on and off the court.

name: Beverly Hills Cop: Axel Foley
summary: The highly anticipated sequel to the classic "Beverly Hills Cop" franchise, "Beverly Hills Cop: Axel F," has received mixed reviews. While some critics praise Eddie Murphy's return to his iconic role and the film's nostalgic appeal, others criticize its formulaic plot and lack of originality. The film attempts to blend action, comedy, and nostalgia, but according to critics, its violence and repetitive humor overshadow the character development and emotional depth that made the original so popular. Despite this, the review from CinemaBlend argues that the film is "way better than you'd expect," suggesting that it offers entertainment value despite its flaws. Overall, the reviews indicate that "Beverly Hills Cop: Axel F" is a polarizing film that will likely appeal to fans of the original while leaving others disappointed.

summary: Michael Rubin's annual 'White Party' in the Hamptons attracted a star-studded guest list, including Tom Brady, Kim Kardashian, and Beyoncé. Rubin, the billionaire CEO of Fanatics, thanked Megan Thee Stallion and others for attending his 2024 All-White Party. The opulent event has become known for its celebrity attendees and lavish festivities, earning it the title of "the most decadent 4th of July party."

name: Rishi Sunak
summary: Rishi Sunak, the former British Prime Minister, faced a likely electoral defeat as he stepped down after his Conservative Party's crushing loss in the election. Despite his last-minute efforts to remain in power, Sunak conceded defeat, apologizing for his party's failure. His departure marks the end of his brief tenure as Prime Minister, marred by economic challenges and internal party divisions. Sunak's resignation comes amid criticism of his policies and a significant financial payout he received despite losing his premiership. The defeat leaves the Conservative Party searching for a new leader and the UK facing political uncertainty.
